Harold Mace was born and raised in Kanab%comma% UT. He was the only professional photographer in the greater Kanab area in the 1940s and 1950s. He was very civic-minded and recorded on film many of the events that happened in Kanab%comma% Kane County%comma% and the Fredonia%comma% Arizona area. He took the children's school pictures and his camera was at many school sports events. He photographed many weddings and family portraits. He also photographed documents for people to be preserved since copy machines were not available. Before he passed away%comma% he donated hundreds of photographs%comma% negatives and his early equipment to the Kanab Heritage Museum so that they could be preserved.

Linford Jr.%comma% an educator%comma% and his wife Mary Hooper Blood Linford %comma% sister of Utah's seventh governor%comma% Henry H. Blood. Also included are the papers of Lorenzo A. Richards%comma% a physicist who specialized in agronomy%comma% and his wife Zilla Linford Richards%comma% niece of Utah's seventh governor%comma% Henry H. Blood. The collections consist of journals%comma% correspondence%comma% day planners%comma% and other materials.
